Key Match Events: Lane Thomas and José Ramírez hit back-to-back homers in the eighth inning to put the Rays away, 6-1.
Joey Cantillo tossed five scoreless innings.
Josh Naylor knocked in two runs with a single in the sixth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Joey Cantillo emphasized the importance of the bats waking up and the team fighting.
Lane Thomas expressed his admiration for José Ramírez's versatility and performance.
Stephen Vogt highlighted the importance of contributions from the entire lineup, not just Ramírez and Naylor.
